<Content>Great location, cheap, and friendly My sister and I booked a twin room with shower at the City Pension Berlin, and were pleasantly surprised with the place. First of all, it's literally right across the street from the Charlottonburg S-bahn stop (2 stops from Zoologischer Garten). Second, it was clean, quiet, and private. After staying in a youth hostel in Amsterdam, it was super-nice to get our own room and shower. In a pension, you don't feel like you have to lock all your stuff up in a little locker for it to be safe; you just put it in the closet. And having a shower was nice - you don't have to run down the hall wearing only a towel. (Note about the shower - you have to push the red button at the shower base for the water to drain.) This pension was cheaper per person per night than our hostel cost us. And to top it all off, the people at the desk are ultra nice, and they serve a quaint yet ample breakfast with fresh flowers and good lighting. Overall, I strongly recommend the City Pension Berlin to travellers who need a break from the hostel scene! 
