<Content>High ceilings, big windows. We too were apprehensive when we arrived, seeing the hotel was near a neon-lit strip club, but once inside we loved it.We had a large clean, double, ensuite room for 72 Euros per night. It had grandiose high ceilings, and huge windows to throw open and watch the world go by. Breakfast is included in the price and was delicious - unlimited juice, crusty rolls, cereals, fruit, toast, pate etc. etc.The staff are predominantly English-speaking, very friendly and helpful. The hotel itself is central, cheap, clean, and excellently connected by U  S Bahn (metro  overground interlinked rail services, stations for both within 2-3 minutes walk) to all parts of the city.Their reception doubles as a bar in the evening, which can be handy for a quiet drink when you get back.You could not find a better base for your stay within this price bracket - I would recommend it to anyone. 
